<br>
I was using a shield with Horn of Hsagra in main hand and taunt in my group was about the same as it was without the shield (Fleshgrinder in Main hand and a Horn of hsagra in offhand normally). My damage output was considerably less but one good weapon was doing a good job of taunting.<br>
<br>
Although a shield isn't as good of an aggro getter as weapons, a warrior might sometimes need to use stuns and being able to use a shield is about the only options for us small warriors. Its a skill that should be maxed like all others.<br>
Suppose you are not main tank and you are on a raid and the raid needs stuns, having a shield and being able to bash with it could be very useful.<br>
It would be great if Verant made a warrior only shield and they gave it a hate proc upon bash. This would change the way warriors look at shields. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cslochraven>CSLochraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/02 12:14:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4516.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Would you use a shield...</span><hr size=1> Haha Shikarii that's old school D2.  Nowadays it's more like Fury Balrog Blade and Stormshield.<br>
